sql:
SELECT plant_type_name, common_name, scientific_name
FROM plant_types
ORDER BY plant_type_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "specific type of soil" refers to soil_id = 1;
- "latest measurements" are determined by the most recent measurement_date;
- "active experiments" are those with a status of 'active'.

- "Average height" refers to the average height of all plants across all experiments;
- "Overall average height" is the mean height of all plants in the `PlantGrowthStats` table;
- "Experiments" are research projects where plants are grown and measured.

- Temperature is measured in degrees Celsius or Fahrenheit;
- Humidity is measured as a percentage;
- Light intensity is measured in lux;
- Soil pH is a measure of the acidity or alkalinity of the soil, typically ranging from 0 to 14;
- Organic matter in soil is measured as a percentage of the total soil mass.

- 'Type A' plants are a specific category of plants in the database;
- 'Higher level of environmental factors' refers to an average environmental value greater than 20;
- 'Time to sprout' is the time to germination.

sql:
SELECT plant_id, height
FROM plant_measurements
WHERE height >= 10.0;

SELECT AVG(JULIANDAY(g.germination_time) - JULIANDAY(g.date_planted)) AS avg_days_to_germination
FROM plants p
INNER JOIN germinations g ON p.plant_id = g.plant_id;

